---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Approach" narrow={true}>
  <section class="intro long-form">
    <h1>Approach</h1>
    <p>
      Good rule does not maintain itself. Even the via negativa, the constraints that separate viable cooperation from parasitic extraction, is itself a via positiva. It must be actively enacted.
    </p>
    <p>
      The work draws on a synthesis of disciplines to build structures of persistence. Looking through all disciplines simultaneously produces a structural clarity that none can achieve in isolation.
    </p>
    <div class="rule"></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>The Synthesis</h2>
    
    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Structural Dynamics</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator">(Robert Fritz)</span>
      </div>
      <p>The engine of the creative process. The creative orientation draws action forward by a clearly held vision of the desired outcome. The path is structural, not motivational.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Natural Law</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator">(Curt Doolittle / Natural Law Institute)</span>
      </div>
      <p>The lens for seeing reality clearly and the constraints for building structures that hold. Decidability: determining what is true, what is reciprocal, what will survive contact with human nature.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Currency Design</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator">(Arthur Brock)</span>
      </div>
      <p>Tools for structuring flows of information, value, obligation, and resources. Reputation, credentialing, mutual obligation, governance all function as currencies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Collective Intelligence</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator"></span>
      </div>
      <p>The capacity to organize and adapt at group scale without requiring central direction for every move.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Operative Traditions</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator">(Miguel Angel Fernandez)</span>
      </div>
      <p>Traditions as active operations, not inherited customs. A tradition is alive when enacted by people who understand its function.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="discipline-block">
      <div class="discipline-header">
        <h3>Formation</h3>
        <span class="discipline-originator"></span>
      </div>
      <p>The embodied dimension. Where the other disciplines become real in human beings. The means by which capability, character, and understanding are transmitted.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Alignment</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <p><strong>This work is for:</strong> Decision-makers willing to do it. People who will build, have hard conversations about what is real, and commit to advance rather than cosmetic change.</p>
    <p><strong>It is not for:</strong> Those who want to automate without understanding, treat transformation as procurement, or seek to extract without reciprocating.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
